    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="327"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Director of War Mobilization</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BJF1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Byrnes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d327fn1">Sent by the White House Map Room, via military
                        channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-26">November 26,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cablegram for the President:</p>
                <p>Increased landing craft program submitted Wednesday<note n="2" xml:id="d327fn2"
                        >November 24, 1943; <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_395">p.
                            395</ref>.</note> possible only if we immediately issue directive giving
                    priority over all programs any kind. Please wire whether I shall have <persName
                        corresp="#p_NDM1">Nelson</persName> issue directive.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d327fn3">For the reply sent by <persName corresp="#p_HHL1"
                            >Hopkins</persName>, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_617">p. 617</ref>. <persName corresp="#p_BJF1"
                            >Byrnes</persName> states (<hi rend="italic">All In One Lifetime</hi>,
                        p. 204) that he sent another telegram to <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> later the same day in which he suggested that the
                        President might count on 15 percent more output than was indicated in the
                        cautious figures in his telegram of November 24, 1943. It has not been
                        possible to find a copy of this additional telegram of November 26 in
                        official files.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
